  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003csection id=\"content-wrapper\" data-content-index=\"1\" data-content-id=\"43961\" data-content-type=\"article\" data-content-form=\"dpf\" data-content-rating=\"pg\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003csection\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\nThere’s just one more thing...\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e \u003cpicture\u003e \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 700px)\" srcset=\"https://s3.crackedcdn.com/phpimages/article/4/2/5/1166425_800x450.jpg\"/\u003e \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://s3.crackedcdn.com/phpimages/article/4/2/5/1166425_320x180.jpg\"/\u003e \u003cimg src=\"https://s3.crackedcdn.com/phpimages/article/4/2/5/1166425_320x180.jpg\" alt=\"Columbo Day Should Be A National Holiday\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e  \u003c/section\u003e \u003carticle\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDid you even realize it’s Columbus Day before you checked your empty mailbox? \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eWhile the holiday is still federally recognized, most Americans have slowly inched away from the occasion, something to do with “atrocities Columbus committed against people living in the Americas.” Some have replaced the day with Indigenous People’s Day, honoring the perseverance and courage of Native American communities. Others are celebrating Columbo Day, contemplating the life and contributions of television detective Lieutenant Frank Columbo. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eIt’s a time, according to Twitter user @LE0_LMA0, “where everyone wears a trench coat and smokes cigars and talks to their dog in complete sentences and stops aging B-list actors from getting away with it.”\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eFor those who observe, these remembrances are for you…\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003carticle id=\"entry-1\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003e\u003clabel\u003e1 \u003c/label\u003e\u003cspa